      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROYAL EDITION (2) turned in a sound effort last time but found a couple better at Townsville over 1400m, beaten 0.7 lengths. That run should have him rock-hard fit now. Sure to go well. OCTOPOLIS (5) has raced twice. Was sixth on debut then clocked-in 3 lengths from the winner in third last time out over 1100m at Mackay. Blinkers added. Hard to beat. SAINT ANNS (4) finished second at Emerald two runs back but was less effective last time over 1100m at Longreach, finishing 9 lengths back in eighth. Faces an easier assignment so she is perfectly placed to score. ELEGANT VENUS (3) missed the placings on debut two runs back then was never in contention last start when 7 lengths away in tenth over 1200m at Townsville. Won't find this as tough so she will be hard to beat.",
